    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breed of dog thought to have originated in Germany, but so poular in France it is the national dog of that country. The poodle was developed as a water retriever, and is clipped with its distinctive coat to increase its efficiency in the water. The poodle has been bred in three size varieties: standard, miniature, and toy. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
